	(40, 30, 'en', 'BOC, BOD and Member of Organization', NULL, '<div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor46" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor46" title="Rich Text Editor, editor46" aria-describedby="cke_719" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><strong>BOARD OF COMMISSIONERS</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor34" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor34" title="Rich Text Editor, editor34" aria-describedby="cke_107" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/GEDE%20PASEK%20SUARDIKA.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/GEDE%20PASEK%20SUARDIKA.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 178px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Dr. GEDE PASEK SUARDIKA, M.Sc.</p><p style="text-align:justify">He was born in Singaraja in August 1963 has served as President Commissioner of PT INKA (Persero) since March 2020. He graduated from the University of Leeds, United Kingdom, with a major in Transportation in 1988 and a Doctorate at Tarumanegara University with a major in Civil Engineering in 2013. He currently serves as Inspector General of the Ministry of Transportation. Previously, he was Director of Land Transportation Safety in 2014, Director of Perum Damri in 2015, General Administration in 2016, Head of Planning Bureau in 2017, Expert Staff of the Ministry of Transportation in the Regional Economy and Partnership of the Ministry of Transportation. The awards he had received were Satya Lancana Karya Satya 10 Years in 2000 and Satya Lancana Karya Satya 20 Years in 2009.<br></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor35" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor35" title="Rich Text Editor, editor35" aria-describedby="cke_158" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/M.%20KHAYAM.png.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/M.%20KHAYAM.png.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 136px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Ir. MUHAMMAD KHAYAM, M.T.</p><p style="text-align:justify">He was born in Jakarta in 1962 has served as Commissioner of PT INKA (Persero) since March 2020. He is a graduate of Chemical Engineering, Bandung Institute of Technology (1990) and continued his education at the Mechanical Engineering Masters Program at the University of Indonesia (2002). Currently he serves as Director General of Chemical, Pharmaceutical and Textile Industries, Ministry of Industry. Previously, he served as Director of Basic Chemical Industry in 2014 - 2016, Director of Upstream Chemical Industry in 2016 - 2018, and Secretary of the Directorate General of Chemical, Pharmaceutical and Textile Industries in 2018 - 2019. He has received several awards, namely Satyalancana Karya Satya X and XX by the President of the Republic of Indonesia in 2001 and 2017.<br></p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor36" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor36" title="Rich Text Editor, editor36" aria-describedby="cke_209" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/2020/Juli%202020/Safri.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/2020/Juli%202020/Safri.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 150px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:16px">Dr. Ir. SAFRI BURHANUDIN, DEA.</span></p><p style="text-align:justify"><span style="font-size:16px"><span style="font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,&quot;sans-serif&quot;">Officially appointed as the Commissioner of PT INKA (Persero) as of October 2017, he is also the Deputy IV in Human Capital Coordination Subject, Science Technology and Nautical Culture in Coordinator Ministry of Nautical Field Republic of Indonesia. He was born in Ujung Pandang in 1961, he achieved his Bachelor Degree of Geology Subject in Padjajaran University and proceeded to Universitie de Bretagne Occidentale, France in Marine Geology Subject and achieved his degree in 1994.</span></span></p><p style="text-align:center"><br></p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders cke_focus" id="editor37" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor37" title="Rich Text Editor, editor37" aria-describedby="cke_260" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Siti_Malkhamah%281%29.png" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Siti_Malkhamah%281%29.png" style="height: 200px; width: 200px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Prof. Ir. SITI MALKHAMAH, M.Sc., Ph.D.</p><p style="text-align:justify">She has been an Independent Commissioner of PT INKA (Persero) since March 2020. His educational background is the Bachelor of Civil Engineering at Gadjah Mada University, continuing his Postgraduate education and his Doctorate degree in Transport Planning and Engineering at the University of Leeds, United Kingdom. She is active in academic activities such as research, community service, scientific publications, seminars and workshops. His books such as the Use of Public Transport for Urban Communities in 2012; Yogyakarta\'s Opportunities and Challenges in the 2013; Yogyakarta Regional Research Council\'s Flower Book Development of Transportation and Technology Sovereignty in Indonesian Human Identity in 2013; and Transportation and Health in&nbsp; “Yogyakarta Sehat Lestari” in 2015.<br></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor45" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor45" title="Rich Text Editor, editor45" aria-describedby="cke_668" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><strong>BOARD OF DIRECTORS</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor38" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor38" title="Rich Text Editor, editor38" aria-describedby="cke_311" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Budi%20Noviantoro_%281%29.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Budi%20Noviantoro_%281%29.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 191px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Ir. BUDI NOVIANTORO</p><p style="text-align:justify">Appointed as President Director of PT INKA (Persero) since January 2018. He is a graduate of Civil Engineering. Department of Hydraulics, Sepuluh November Institute of Technology Surabaya in 1985. Previous history of Director of Logistics and Business Development of PT KAI (2014) and Ad Interim President Director of PT KAI (2018).</p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor39" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor39" title="Rich Text Editor, editor39" aria-describedby="cke_362" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Andy%20Budiman.jpeg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Andy%20Budiman.jpeg" style="height: 200px; width: 184px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">ANDY BUDIMAN SE., A.k.</p><p style="text-align:justify">Appointed as Finance and HR Director of PT INKA (Persero) since March 2020. He pioneered a career as a young auditor on the Finance Ministry BPKP Joint Team in 1990, Member of Corruption Eradication in 2005-2007, KPK investigator in 2007-2011, as Project Manager PT Sarana Multi Infrastruktur (Persero) Geothermal Project Management Unit in 2016-2018. Finance Director of PT Nindya Beton in 2018-2019 and Associate Director of PT PPA Kapital from June 2019 to March 2020. He is a graduate of University of Indonesia Accounting and D-IV Accountancy at the State College of Accountancy.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor40" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor40" title="Rich Text Editor, editor40" aria-describedby="cke_413" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Agung%20Sedaju%20closeup.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/Agung%20Sedaju%20closeup.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 193px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Ir. AGUNG SEDAJU, M.T.</p><p style="text-align:justify">Appointed as Development Director of PT INKA (Persero) since January 2018. He began his career at PT INKA (Persero) since 1996, he served as General Manager of Marketing in 2011, General Manager of Human Capital Division in 2012, General Manager of Logistics Division in 2014, General Manager of the Technology Division in 2015, and Commissioner of PT INKA Multi Solusi Consulting in 2018. He graduated with a Bachelor of Physics Engineering at the Bandung Institute of Technology in 1995 and a Masters in Electrical Engineering at the Ten November Institute of Technology Surabaya in 2006.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-4"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor41" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor41" title="Rich Text Editor, editor41" aria-describedby="cke_464" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/I%20GEDE%20AGUS%20PRAYATNA.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/I%20GEDE%20AGUS%20PRAYATNA.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 132px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Ir. I GEDE AGUS PRAYATNA</p><p style="text-align:justify">Appointed as Director of Operations of PT INKA (Persero) since March 2020. He began his career as an employee of PT INKA (Persero) at the Technology Center in 1993, as Head of Project Engineering in 1998, Assistant Manager of Commercial and Technology Division in 2004, Manager of the Private Marketing Department and Exports in 2008, General Manager of Railroad Marketing from 2013 to 2018 and Managing Director of PT INKA Multi Solusi Trading from January 2018 to March 2020. He graduated from Mechanical Engineering at Udayana University in 1992.</p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor44" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor44" title="Rich Text Editor, editor44" aria-describedby="cke_617" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><strong>CORPORATE MEMBER</strong></p></div></div></div></div><div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor42" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor42" title="Rich Text Editor, editor42" aria-describedby="cke_515" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/P%281%29.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/P%281%29.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 355px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">Ir. PUGUH DWI TJAHJONO</p><p style="text-align:justify">Graduated from Mechanical Engineering Bachelor, Institut Teknologi Sepuluh Nopember Surabaya in 1997. Appointed as General Manager of Corporate Secretary at PT INKA (Persero) since February 2019. Started career at PT INKA (Persero) since 1999 which previously as General Manager Human Capital in 2017 and President Director of PT INKA Multi Solution (Subsidiary of PT INKA) in 2018.</p></div></div></div><div class="col-sm-6"><div class="type"><div class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders" id="editor43" spellcheck="false" style="position: relative;" role="textbox" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor43" title="Rich Text Editor, editor43" aria-describedby="cke_566" contenteditable="false"><p style="text-align:center"><img alt="" data-cke-saved-src="/kcfinder/upload/images/M.jpg" src="/kcfinder/upload/images/M.jpg" style="height: 200px; width: 355px;"><br></p><p style="text-align:center">SARMIATUN, M.M., CA.</p><p style="text-align:justify">Appointed as General Manager of Internal Audit of PT INKA (Persero) since July 2017. She graduated from Accounting of Brawijaya University and continued her Master\'s Degree in Economics and Business at Gajah Mada University. She started a career in PT INKA (Persero) since 1992 with previous position is Director of PT INKA Multi Solution which is&nbsp; subsidiary company since 2015 until 2016.</p></div></div></div></div>', 47, 0, NULL, NULL, '2018-01-10 02:38:00', '2020-07-03 00:24:56', NULL),
	(41, 30, 'en', 'Division', 2, '<div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div class="image-wrapper"><img src="/kcfinder/upload/images/2020/Juli%202020/korporasi%20-%20edit%20eng%201.jpg"><div class="image-caption"></div></div></div></div></div>\r\n		    \r\n		    <div class="row section"><div class="col-sm-12"><div class="type"><div title="Rich Text Editor, editor20" class="text-wrapper cke_editable cke_editable_inline cke_contents_ltr cke_show_borders cke_focus" id="editor20" role="textbox" aria-describedby="cke_59" style="position: relative;" spellcheck="false" aria-label="Rich Text Editor, editor20" contenteditable="false"><table style="width:700px" class=" cke_show_border" data-cke-table-faked-selection-table="" cellspacing="1" cellpadding="1" border="0"><tbody><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>MAIN DIRECTORATE</strong><br></td></tr><tr><td>Corporate Secretary</td><td>:&nbsp; Puguh Dwi Tjahjono<br></td></tr><tr><td>Internal Audit</td><td>:&nbsp; Sarmiatun</td></tr><tr><td><br></td><td><br></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>DIRECTORATE OF FINANCE &amp; HUMAN RESOURCES</strong></td></tr><tr><td>Finance &amp; Accounting<br></td><td>:&nbsp; Budi Wahyunarto&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br></td></tr><tr><td>Human Capital &amp; General Affairs<br></td><td>:&nbsp; Arif Muhaimin</td></tr><tr><td><br></td><td><br></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>DIRECTORATE OF DEVELOPMENT</strong><br></td></tr><tr><td>Technology</td><td>:&nbsp; Hery Prasetya<br></td></tr><tr><td>Research &amp; Development<br></td><td>:&nbsp; Junaidi<br></td></tr><tr><td><br></td><td><br></td></tr><tr><td colspan="2"><strong>DIRECTORATE OF OPERATION</strong><br></td></tr><tr><td>Marketing<br></td><td>:&nbsp; Wai Wahdan<br></td></tr><tr><td>Production Planning &amp; Service Provision<br></td><td>:&nbsp; Suwun Setyanto<br></td></tr>